SB 1587-4
(LC 83)
2/11/26 (DFY/ps)
Requested by Senator CAMPOS
PROPOSED AMENDMENTS TO
SENATE BILL 1587
1 Delete lines 4 through 25 of the printed bill and insert:
2 “SECTION 1. (1) As used in this section:
3 “(a) ‘Data broker’ has the meaning given that term in ORS
4 646A.593.
5 “(b) ‘Personally identifiable information’ has the meaning given
6 that term in ORS 432.005.
7 “(c) ‘Public body’ has the meaning given that term in ORS 174.109.
8 “(2)(a) Except as provided in subsection (3) of this section, a public
9 body may not disclose personally identifiable information to a data
10 broker unless the data broker first provides a written attestation to
11 the public body that the information will not be sold or otherwise
12 transferred to any entity that will use the information to enforce fed-
13 eral immigration law.
14 “(b) If a public body reasonably believes that a data broker’s written
15 attestation contains material misrepresentations, falsehoods or omis-
16 sions, the public body shall reject the written attestation and shall
17 decline to disclose personally identifiable information to the data bro-
18 ker.
19 “(3) This section does not prohibit a public body from disclosing
20 personally identifiable information to a data broker if the disclosure
21 is required under ORS 192.311 to 192.478 or required by an order of a

1 court of competent jurisdiction.
2 “SECTION 2. This 2026 Act being necessary for the immediate
3 preservation of the public peace, health and safety, an emergency is
4 declared to exist, and this 2026 Act takes effect on its passage.”.
5
